race.comment: HOLY CROWN (9) ran a strong race last time out, finishing third and beaten only 0.7 lengths over 1200m at Rockhampton. Best figures measure up and is sure to run well. SAVVY SONG (6) finished 7 lengths from the winner in ninth over 1000m at Toowoomba last start. This looks an easier test than last time and on his best form he is one of the key runners. TOUGH JUDGE (2) is close to breaking through, last start finishing just a neck away in second over 1200m at Charleville. Looks well placed so expect a big run this time. KOBE ASCOT (1) couldn't sustain the effort at Charleville last time out but his form prior was very strong. Happy to overlook one poor effort and expect him to bounce back.
